From Ndubuisi Orji, Abuja The House of Representatives, on Tuesday, invited the Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola, and his counterpart in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Geoffrey Onyeama, to brief it on issues relating to the ordeal of former Deputy Senate President Ike Ekweremadu and his wife, Nwanneka, who are detained London. Also to brief the House through its relevant committees is the acting Comptroller General of Immigration, Issa Jere. Ekweremadu and his wife were detained in London last week over an alleged “conspiracy to arrange and facilitate the travel of another person with a view to exploitation namely organ harvesting.”